// pending ņāüĒā£ņŚÉņä£ 5ļČä(300ņ┤ł) ņ┤łĻ│╝ ņŗ£ ņ×ÉļÅÖ ļ¦īļŻī
function _expireOldTrades(sheet) {
  const last = sheet.getLastRow();
  if (last < SCHEMA.TRADES.dataStartRow) return;
  const col = getTradesColumns_(sheet);
  const rows = getTradesRows_(sheet);
  const now  = Date.now();
  const TIMEOUT_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000; // 5ļČä
  let changed = false;
  rows.forEach((row, i) => {
    if (String(row[col.status]) !== 'pending') return;
    const createdAt = new Date(String(row[col.createdAt])).getTime();
    if (isNaN(createdAt) || now - createdAt < TIMEOUT_MS) return;
    row[col.status] = 'ņŗżĒī© (ņŗ£Ļ░ä ņ┤łĻ│╝)';
    row[col.resolvedAt] = new Date().toISOString();
    changed = true;
  });
  if (changed) {
    sheet.getRange(SCHEMA.TRADES.dataStartRow, col.status + 1, rows.length, 3).setValues(rows.map(function(r) {
      return [r[col.status], r[col.createdAt], r[col.resolvedAt]];
    }));
  }
}

function getTrades(userId) {
  const lock = LockService.getScriptLock();
  try { lock.waitLock(10000); } catch(e) { return { ok: false, error: 'ņ×Āņŗ£ Ēøä ļŗżņŗ£ ņŗ£ļÅäĒĢ┤ņŻ╝ņäĖņÜö.' }; }

  try {
  const sheet = getOrCreateTradesSheet();
  const last  = sheet.getLastRow();
  if (last < SCHEMA.TRADES.dataStartRow) return { ok: true, incoming: [], outgoing: [] };
  const col = getTradesColumns_(sheet);

  _expireOldTrades(sheet);
  const rows = getTradesRows_(sheet);
  const incoming = [], outgoing = [];
  rows.forEach(row => {
    if (!row[col.id]) return;
    const t = {
      id: String(row[col.id]), requester: String(row[col.requester]),
      requesterCardId: Number(row[col.requesterCardId]), requesterCardName: String(row[col.requesterCardName]),
      target: String(row[col.target]),
      targetCardId: Number(row[col.targetCardId]), targetCardName: String(row[col.targetCardName]),
      status: String(row[col.status]), createdAt: String(row[col.createdAt]), resolvedAt: String(row[col.resolvedAt]),
      requesterPrayed: !!row[col.requesterPrayed], targetPrayed: !!row[col.targetPrayed]
    };
    if (t.target   === userId) incoming.push(t);
    if (t.requester === userId) outgoing.push(t);
  });
  incoming.sort((a, b) => b.createdAt.localeCompare(a.createdAt));
  outgoing.sort((a, b) => b.createdAt.localeCompare(a.createdAt));

  // ņÖäļŻīļÉ£ ĻĄÉĒÖśņŚÉ ņāüļīĆļ░® H&P ĻĖ░ļÅäņĀ£ļ¬® ņ▓©ļČĆ
  // Users ņŗ£ĒŖĖņŚÉņä£ ļŗēļäżņ×äŌåÆņŗżļ¬ģ ņŗżņŗ£Ļ░ä ņĪ░ĒÜī ŌåÆ ĻĖ░ļÅäņĀ£ļ¬® ļ¦żņ╣Ł
  const hasAccepted = [...incoming, ...outgoing].some(function(t) { return t.status === 'accepted'; });
  if (hasAccepted) {
    const hpEntries = getYouthHpEntries();
    const nickToName = getUserNameMap_();
    [...incoming, ...outgoing].forEach(function(t) {
      if (t.status === 'accepted') {
        const otherNick = (t.target === userId) ? t.requester : t.target;
        const realName = nickToName[otherNick] || '';
        const entry = realName ? hpEntries.find(function(e) { return e.n === realName; }) : null;
        t.otherPrayer = entry ? entry.c : '';
      }
    });
  }

  return { ok: true, incoming, outgoing };
  } finally {
    lock.releaseLock();
  }
}

